ED  - Guillaumet, JL
ED  - Belin, M
ED  - Puig, H
TI  - Recent changes in the vegetation in the region of the dense ombrophilous forest of Santa Catarina, Brazil
T2  - TROPICAL PHYOTOGEOGRAPHY: REALITIES AND PERSPECTIVES
CP  - International Colloquium on Tropical Phytogeography, Dedicated to Raymond Schnell
AB  - The atlantic rain forest covered until the XVIIIth century almost all the littoral zone of the Brasilian stale of Santa Catarina. Nowadays only relictual occurrence of the forest can be found on the upper slopes of mountains. The valleys and slopes are now taken by agriculture and pasturage. By periodical abandonment of agricultural activities different secondary successional stages cover the slopes as mosaics. The source of the floristic elements which compose those formations are very different ecotopes like dunes, mountain summits, gaps, rocks and outland. As a result we observe very recent associations dominated by a small number of species in each successional stage. A parcial recuperation of the forest should be ensured by the fast successional dynamics which occurs on less lixiviated soils, by the availability of sufficient seed-trees and dispersers and by a conservation and management policy based on the maintenance of the climaxic forest structure and biodiversity.
