TI  - The importance of secondary forests and the impacts of their substitution by large-scale mechanized grain cultivation in the Amazon region
T2  - INTERCIENCIA
AB  - The teen "degraded lands" leas been used to refer to secondary; or regenerated, forests in the Brazilian Amazon. Both government and private enterprise have proposed the mechanized cultivation of grains, specially so bean, maize, and rice, as an alternative utilization of these areas, considered prima facie to be degraded and unproductive. An analysis of the importance of Amazonian second-growth forests was undertaken front ecological, social and economic points of view, and the impacts are discussed of their proposed substitution by large-scale mechanized grain cultivation.
